messages.message:
Hey, for some reason the Visual Reasoning field seems to swap the letters on the car names in this doc very often - despite getting everything else right. Any idea why this is?
https://aihub.instabase.com/build/0195aa06-0cf9-7ea8-9e1a-1840970f035a

run: https://aihub.instabase.com/review/0bba2a85-2544-4181-8d2c-26f997680e0a

cc @jordy.vlan
It has a bias toward A being the culprit :stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye: no, honestly no idea. We just return the result from the VLM as is, so there should not be anything different.
Did you change the prompt? It is looking better now?
I didn't change the prompt - but I did see it sometimes getting the right answer. At runtime I haven't seen in doing well with the previous prompt though
TBH I think visual reasoning is prone to high levels of hallucinations when it comes to analyzing characters. This is just a consequence
